LASSA FEVER - SOUTH AFRICA EX NIGERIA: CORRECTION
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>


Date: 28 Apr 2009
From: Lucille Blumberg <lucilleb@nicd.ac.za> [Edited]

We are concerned about the posting [20090425.1554] on Lassa fever in
a physician, imported into South Africa ex Nigeria. This case
actually occurred two years ago and was reported to Promed then. The
posting refers to 22nd April 2009.

--
Prof Janusz Paweska, Head of the Special Pathogens Unit
Dr Lucille Blumberg, Deputy Director and head of the Epidemiology Division
Medical Consultant to the Special Pathogens Unit
National Institute for Communicable Diseases
No 1 Modderfontein Road
Sandringham
Johannesburg
<lucilleb@nicd.ac.za>

[ProMED thanks Prof. Paweska and Dr. Blumberg for bringing this
serious error to our attention and apologizes for inadvertently
posting a 2-year old news story. - Mod.LM]
